article.headline: Delaware St. 73, Winston-Salem 50
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- Donald Johnson scored 22 points to lead Delaware State to a 73-50 victory over Winston-Salem State on Monday night. Frisco Sandidge added 21 points and nine rebounds for the Hornets (3-14), who never trailed, to snap a five-game losing streak. It was the 12th road game of the season for Winston-Salem (4-10), which is 2-10 away from home. Delaware State led 26-17 at halftime and 46-31 on Johnson's layup with 10:30 remaining in the game. Tramaine Johnson's free throw gave the Hornets a 60-39 lead with 5:51 left. Fred Bouie added 10 points for the Hornets, who were 24 of 48 from the field (50 percent). Jamal Durham scored 13 points to lead the Rams, who shot just 48 percent from the line (12 of 25). Brian Fisher added 10 points.
